# Construction de la variable `niveau_educ`

## Recodage en 5 catégories ordonnées

La variable `s2aq9` contient la classe/année atteinte. Le tableau suivant présente
la correspondance appliquée pour construire les 5 niveaux :

```{r recodage-table, echo=FALSE}
data.frame(
  `Codes s2aq9`  = c("0, 1-3, 51, 52, 61",
                     "11 a 16",
                     "21, 22, 23, 321",
                     "24, 25, 26, 27, 28, 322",
                     "31, 33-35, 41, 43, 411-424"),
  `Niveau`       = c("Aucun","Primaire","Junior Secondary",
                     "Senior Secondary","Tertiaire")
) %>%
  kable(booktabs = TRUE, align = c("l","l"),
        caption = "Correspondance codes s2aq9 -- niveaux d'éducation",
        col.names = c("Codes s2aq9", "Niveau d'education")) %>%
  kable_styling(latex_options = c("hold_position","striped"),
                font_size = 9, full_width = FALSE) %>%
  row_spec(0, bold = TRUE, background = "#1a5276", color = "white")
```

```{r niveau-educ}
educ_data <- educ_data %>%
  mutate(
    niveau_educ = case_when(
      s2aq9 == 0                        ~ "Aucun",
      s2aq9 %in% c(1,2,3,51,52,61)     ~ "Aucun",
      s2aq9 %in% 11:16                  ~ "Primaire",
      s2aq9 %in% c(21,22,23,321)        ~ "Junior Secondary",
      s2aq9 %in% c(24,25,26,27,28,322)  ~ "Senior Secondary",
      s2aq9 %in% c(31,33,34,35,41,43,
                   411,412,421,422,
                   423,424)             ~ "Tertiaire",
      TRUE                              ~ NA_character_
    ),
    niveau_educ = factor(
      niveau_educ,
      levels  = c("Aucun","Primaire","Junior Secondary",
                  "Senior Secondary","Tertiaire"),
      ordered = TRUE
    )
  )
```

## Fréquences et proportions

```{r freq-educ}
freq_educ <- educ_data %>%
  filter(!is.na(niveau_educ)) %>%
  count(niveau_educ) %>%
  mutate(prop = n / sum(n) * 100) %>%
